                                <p>
                                    Dear Delegates,
                                </p>
                                <p>Welcome to the Indian Parliament; a place where shoes are flung, microphones are broken and history is made. I will be serving as the speaker of this glorious body of the Lok Sabha in DSMUN ’16.</p>
                                <p>Before I go on talking of the committee, a little about myself. I first started MUN’ing back in the 9th grade as a member of the media team here at DSMUN. Since then MUN has taken me from France in 1789 to China in 2030. Aside from MUN, my interests lie in playing the Saxophone, quizzing and of course politics.</p>
                                <p>Politics is an art which every human lives by, some voluntarily do so while some don’t, however it governs every individual’s thinking and decision making. While representing your various parties and constituencies, you must all keep in mind the essentials for politics. As representatives of not only your political parties but also of the people of our country, it must be everybody’s prerogative to ensure the welfare of our great nation. The Indian Parliament is an amalgamation of some of the most diverse individuals, not just by cultures but by ideologies as well. It is because of the presence of these differences that I must remind you all of the existence of the extremely fine line between a democracy and an anarchy, as well as the very fine line between an autocracy and a democracy. Therefore, be outspoken however for the betterment of your own constituents before your own personal prejudices as the assembly is only as strong as its members.</p>
                                <p>I hope you share my excitement to be a part of this Assembly and that you shall do your best to ensure that this committee is brimming with intellectual debate, diplomatic negotiations and a fair share of entertainment. My email is given below so feel free to email me with any queries.</p>
